						<summary>

						<p>States that <hi rend="bold">Anavōta's</hi> minister <hi rend="bold">Sōmaya</hi> issued a proclamation giving certain assurances to traders resorting to the port of <hi rend="bold">Mōṭupalli</hi> for trade purposes, remitting the customs duties (?) known as <hi rend="italic">aputrikam</hi> and <hi rend="italic">kaḍḍāyamu,</hi> the duties on gold, one-third of the duty on <hi rend="italic">gandhamu vaḷubaḍi</hi> and agreeing to charge duty on other articles at the old rates.</p>						

						<p>Face A.</p>						

						</summary>
